radiographic_examinations.findings: Two hypodense lesions in the liver in segment VIII measuring 1.7 cm and 2.0 cm are unchanged from prior ultrasound; small cyst or hemangioma at inferior liver; kidneys enhance symmetrically without hydronephrosis; tiny hypodensities in the right kidney measuring up to 8 mm; appendix filled with stool and air with an air-fluid level in the mid portion but a normal tip, mild adjacent stranding in the right lower quadrant; 2.0cm left ovarian cyst; enhancing fibroids in the uterus; no free fluid in abdomen or pelvis.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Two hypodense lesions in the liver are unchanged from prior ultrasound; tiny hypodensities in the right kidney similar to prior; no new liver lesion is identified.
